    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory corruption in F1AP setup response handling\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP setup response memory management functions contained several critical bugs that could lead to memory corruption and crashes under certain conditions. \n\nThe primary issue was in `free_f1ap_setup_response()` which incorrectly checked `SI_container_length > 0` instead of verifying the pointer was non-NULL before freeing. This could cause crashes when attempting to free already-freed memory or invalid pointers.\n\nAdditionally, there was an indexing bug in `free_f1ap_cu_configuration_update()` where the wrong loop variable was used, causing out-of-bounds array access.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high load conditions with multiple gNB-DU connections:\n1. F1 setup responses with NULL `gNB_CU_name` field cause segfault in `free()` \n2. F1 setup responses with zero-length SI containers cause double-free corruption\n3. CU configuration updates with multiple cells trigger array bounds violation\n\nThese issues manifest as intermittent crashes in the F1AP management plane during DU registration procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.c`: Fixed NULL pointer checks and double-free in setup response handler\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.c`: Corrected array indexing bug in CU configuration update freeing\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.h`: Updated function signatures for consistency\n"
}